      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The current American economic structure is not a meritocracy; it is a meticulously engineered system that perpetuates racial subjugation through entrenched wealth disparities. To claim that the gap between white and Black Americans is merely a result of individual choices is a willful blindness to centuries of institutionalized theft and discriminatory policy. Therefore, wealth redistribution is not a radical proposal, but the only logical and morally imperative mechanism to dismantle a system that was built on racial exploitation.\n\nThe foundational problem lies in the historical architecture of American capitalism, which systematically denied Black and Brown communities access to the primary engines of wealth creation. Practices like discriminatory lending, segregated housing, and unequal educational funding were not isolated incidents; they were deliberate state actions that starved minority populations of generational capital. Only through aggressive wealth redistribution can we begin to counteract the massive, inherited deficit created by this deliberate, state-sanctioned racial theft.",
      "source": "target",
